subsection.text:
It is the sense of Congress that, in any contract requiring the Institute of Medicine of the National Academies to convene a committee to study the health of Gulf War veterans, the Secretary of Veterans Affairs should ensure that any such committee convened should contain not less than three members of the Research Advisory Committee on Gulf War Veterans' Illnesses established by
section 707 of the Veterans Health Care Act of 1992 ( Public Law 102–585 ;
38 U.S.C. 527 note).
